    "Most of the prediction mechanisms utilize motion-based techniques to predict future movements according to the existing position of human body joints or points, and these techniques correct the errors attained among the estimated and original measurements.",
    "These techniques perform well when sufficient information is attained from the previous movements which are precisely modeled by the underlying motion mechanism.Key contributions of the developed human motion intention-based prediction model are listed as follows.• To implement an efficient hybridized mechanism for the human motion intention prediction model to help physically challenged individuals recognize human behavior and predict future body poses in a complicated environment.",
